  <section class="hero">
    <h1>Migration Parity</h1>
    <p class="muted">OpenQuant-rs migration tracks mlfinlab behavior with explicit test crosswalks and fixture-backed parity checks.</p>
  </section>

  <h2>Ground Truth Sources</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><code>tests/crosswalk.md</code>: Python-to-Rust test mapping and status.</li>
    <li><code>ROADMAP.md</code>: synchronized task planning record.</li>
    <li>Beads/Second Brain: issue-level execution and closure tracking.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Current State</h2>
  <p>Tracked module parity is complete for the migration scope. Validation and production baseline workflows are now the primary operational focus.</p>

  <h2>When You Still Need mlfinlab Locally</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Generating new fixtures from Python behavior.</li>
    <li>Backfilling parity for newly scoped upstream modules.</li>
    <li>Investigating behavior drift against upstream changes.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>When You Do Not Need mlfinlab Locally</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Normal use of OpenQuant-rs as a Rust library.</li>
    <li>Running existing tests and benchmarks.</li>
    <li>Maintaining release workflows and docs.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Parity Change Protocol</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>Add or update fixture inputs under <code>tests/fixtures/</code>.</li>
    <li>Port/extend Rust tests under <code>crates/openquant/tests/</code>.</li>
    <li>Update <code>tests/crosswalk.md</code> and associated tracking items.</li>
    <li>Document notable numerical tolerance differences in test notes.</li>
  </ol>
</Layout>
